data.name: radioSingle.ToolTip
data.value: Create a single file including all transitions. If this is not just for reference, make sure your instrument can handle the full set of transitions.

data.name: radioProtein.ToolTip
data.value: Split methods along protein boundaries. If this is not just for reference, make sure your instrument can handle the number of transitions in each file.

data.name: radioBuckets.ToolTip
data.value: Create as many files as needed, given constraints on transition count.

data.name: textMaxTransitions.ToolTip
data.value: Each file created will have at most this number of transitions, but may have fewer, if peptide or protein boundaries do not allow the maximum.

data.name: comboTargetType.ToolTip
data.value: Type of method to export. Standard will export an unscheduled method. Triggered will export a method where secondary transitions will not be measured until primary transitions reach a certain intensity threshold.

data.name: textRunLength.ToolTip
data.value: Run length of the entire gradient in minutes, required for unscheduled Thermo and Waters methods.

data.name: textDwellTime.ToolTip
data.value: Dwell time per transition in milliseconds, required for unscheduled Agilent and SCIEX methods.

data.name: comboInstrument.ToolTip
data.value: Instrument type on which these settings will run

data.name: textTemplateFile.ToolTip
data.value: Existing method file containing settings that will be used in the exported method. A single template transition may also be required for transition values not controled by Skyline.

data.name: cbIgnoreProteins.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, peptides are distributed among files without regard to the protein boundaries. Otherwise, peptides in the same protein will only be split, if the protein contains more than the maximum number of transitions.

data.name: cbEnergyRamp.ToolTip
data.value: Add Energy Ramp column required by some version of Thermo TSQ software

data.name: cbTriggerRefColumns.ToolTip
data.value: Add Trigger and Reference columns required by some version of Thermo TSQ software

data.name: cbExportMultiQuant.ToolTip
data.value: Exports a MultiQuant compatible analysis method to the same directory and base name as the Analyst acquisition method.

data.name: cbUseStartAndEndRts.ToolTip
data.value: Exports a start and end time, rather than a retention time and a window.

data.name: comboPolarityFilter.ToolTip
data.value: Controls export behavior for documents with both positive and negative transitions. Allows for output of only positive or only negative transitions, or creates separate outputs for each polarity.

data.name: cbTune3.ToolTip
data.value: Output in a format compatible with Tune v3 and higher.

data.name: cbSortByMz.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, the exported method is ordered by m/z values in ascending order (precursor m/z, then product m/z when applicable) for optimized quadrupole switching.

data.name: cbSlens.ToolTip
data.value: Write the S-lens column for Thermo instruments. For transitions without an explicit S-lens value, 50 is used.

data.name: comboTuning.ToolTip
data.value: Level of tuning to use when optimizing for compensation voltages.

data.name: cbExportEdcMass.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, exports Enhanced Duty Cycle (EDC) values for Waters methods. These values will be the m/z of the top ranked transition of the precursor. If unchecked, zeros will be written in their place.

data.name: cbWriteCoV.ToolTip
data.value: Write the FAIMS compensation voltage column for Thermo TSQ instruments.

data.name: textPrimaryCount.ToolTip
data.value: The number of transitions to make primary when exporting a triggered method.

data.name: textMs1RepetitionTime.ToolTip
data.value: The maximum time allowed between MS1 spectrum acquisition interspersed between MS/MS spectra for PRM (default 10 ms)
